Barplot

specie <- c(rep("sorgho" , 3) , rep("poacee" , 3) , rep("banana" , 3) , rep("triticum" , 3) )
condition <- rep(c("normal" , "stress" , "Nitrogen") , 4)
value <- abs(rnorm(12 , 0 , 15))
data <- data.frame(specie,condition,value)

specie <- c(rep("sorgho" , 3) , rep("poacee" , 3) , rep("banana" , 3) , rep("triticum" , 3) )
condition <- rep(c("normal" , "stress" , "Nitrogen") , 4)
value <- abs(rnorm(12 , 0 , 15))
data <- data.frame(specie,condition,value)

head(data)
##   specie condition     value
## 1 sorgho    normal  6.484271
## 2 sorgho    stress 11.077923
## 3 sorgho  Nitrogen 25.093143
## 4 poacee    normal 12.962721
## 5 poacee    stress 15.953740
## 6 poacee  Nitrogen  4.407755
# Stacked
ggplot(data, aes(fill=condition, y=value, x=specie)) + 
    geom_bar(position="stack", stat="identity")

# Nicer with viridis
ggplot(data, aes(fill=condition, y=value, x=specie)) + 
    geom_bar(position="stack", stat="identity") +
    scale_fill_viridis(discrete = T) +
    ggtitle("Studying 4 species..") +
    xlab("")

# With faceting
ggplot(data, aes(fill=condition, y=value, x=condition)) + 
    geom_bar(position="dodge", stat="identity") +
    scale_fill_viridis(discrete = T, option = "E") +
    ggtitle("Studying 4 species..") +
    facet_wrap(~specie) +
    theme(legend.position="none") +
    xlab("")

Plotting with error bars

# Lets use the Toothpaste data in R
df <- ToothGrowth
df$dose <- as.factor(df$dose) #factorize dose for plotting reasons

head(df)
##    len supp dose
## 1  4.2   VC  0.5
## 2 11.5   VC  0.5
## 3  7.3   VC  0.5
## 4  5.8   VC  0.5
## 5  6.4   VC  0.5
## 6 10.0   VC  0.5
# create summary stats for your data
df.summary <- df %>%
  group_by(dose) %>%
  summarise(
    sd = sd(len, na.rm = TRUE),
    len = mean(len))

head(df.summary)
## # A tibble: 3 × 3
##   dose     sd   len
##   <fct> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 0.5    4.50  10.6
## 2 1      4.42  19.7
## 3 2      3.77  26.1
# create simple ggplot with error bars
ggplot(df.summary, aes(x = dose, y = len, ymin = len-sd, ymax = len+sd)) +
  geom_errorbar(width = 0.2) +
  geom_point(size = 1.5)

# Cooler plots with the data
head(df)
##    len supp dose
## 1  4.2   VC  0.5
## 2 11.5   VC  0.5
## 3  7.3   VC  0.5
## 4  5.8   VC  0.5
## 5  6.4   VC  0.5
## 6 10.0   VC  0.5
ggplot(df, aes(dose, len)) +
  geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(0.2), color = "darkgray") + 
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = len-sd, ymax = len+sd),width=0.2, data = df.summary)

# Line plot
ggplot(df.summary, aes(dose, len)) +
  geom_line(aes(group = 1)) +
  geom_errorbar( aes(ymin = len-sd, ymax = len+sd),width = 0.2) +
  geom_point(size = 2)

# Bar plot
ggplot(df.summary, aes(dose, len)) +
  geom_col(fill = "lightgray", color = "black") +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = len, ymax = len+sd), width = 0.2) 

# individual jitter points + error bars 
ggplot(df, aes(dose, len)) +
  geom_jitter( position = position_jitter(0.2), color = "darkgray") + 
  geom_line(aes(group = 1), data = df.summary) +
  geom_errorbar(
    aes(ymin = len-sd, ymax = len+sd),
    data = df.summary, width = 0.2) +
  geom_point(data = df.summary, size = 2)

# Bar plots of means + individual jitter points + errors
ggplot(df, aes(dose, len)) +
  geom_col(data = df.summary, fill = NA, color = "black") +
  geom_jitter( position = position_jitter(0.2), color = "black") + 
  geom_errorbar( aes(ymin = len-sd, ymax = len+sd), 
                 data = df.summary, width = 0.2) 

# Grouped data
# create a new summary based the groups

df.summary2 <- df %>%
  group_by(dose, supp) %>%
  summarise(
    sd = sd(len),
    len = mean(len)
  )
df.summary2
## # A tibble: 6 × 4
## # Groups:   dose [3]
##   dose  supp     sd   len
##   <fct> <fct> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 0.5   OJ     4.46 13.2 
## 2 0.5   VC     2.75  7.98
## 3 1     OJ     3.91 22.7 
## 4 1     VC     2.52 16.8 
## 5 2     OJ     2.66 26.1 
## 6 2     VC     4.80 26.1
# Plots
ggplot(df.summary2, aes(dose, len)) +
  geom_errorbar(
    aes(ymin = len-sd, ymax = len+sd, color = supp),
    position = position_dodge(0.3), width = 0.2)+
  geom_point(aes(color = supp), position = position_dodge(0.3))

# Line plot + error bars
ggplot(df.summary2, aes(dose, len)) +
  geom_line(aes(linetype = supp, group = supp))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_errorbar(
    aes(ymin = len-sd, ymax = len+sd, group = supp),
     width = 0.2)

ggplot(df, aes(dose, len, color = supp)) +
  geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(0.2)) + 
  geom_line(aes(group = supp),data = df.summary2) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = len-sd, ymax = len+sd), data = df.summary2, width = 0.2)

# Bar plots + jittered points + error bars
ggplot(df, aes(dose, len, fill = supp)) +
  geom_col(data = df.summary2, position = position_dodge(0.8),width = 0.7) +
  geom_jitter(position = position_jitterdodge(jitter.width = 0.2, dodge.width = 0.8)) + 
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = len-sd, ymax = len+sd), data = df.summary2,
                width = 0.2, position = position_dodge(0.8))

P-value on plot

library(ggsignif)

# Basic Example
df <- mpg
head(df)
## # A tibble: 6 × 11
##   manufacturer model displ  year   cyl trans      drv     cty   hwy fl    class 
##   <chr>        <chr> <dbl> <int> <int> <chr>      <chr> <int> <int> <chr> <chr> 
## 1 audi         a4      1.8  1999     4 auto(l5)   f        18    29 p     compa…
## 2 audi         a4      1.8  1999     4 manual(m5) f        21    29 p     compa…
## 3 audi         a4      2    2008     4 manual(m6) f        20    31 p     compa…
## 4 audi         a4      2    2008     4 auto(av)   f        21    30 p     compa…
## 5 audi         a4      2.8  1999     6 auto(l5)   f        16    26 p     compa…
## 6 audi         a4      2.8  1999     6 manual(m5) f        18    26 p     compa…
# create sub data with only two variables
df1 <- df %>% filter(class == c("compact", "pickup"))

# plot with p-value
ggplot(df1, aes(class, hwy, fill = class)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  geom_signif(test = "t.test",
    comparisons = list(c("compact", "pickup")),
    map_signif_level = F)

# plot with significance
ggplot(df1, aes(class, hwy, fill = class)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  geom_signif(test = "t.test",
    comparisons = list(c("compact", "pickup")),
    map_signif_level = T)

# You can select your comparisons and stat test
ggplot(mpg, aes(class, hwy, fill = class)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  geom_signif(test = "t.test",
    comparisons = list(
      c("compact", "pickup"),
      c("subcompact", "suv")),
  map_signif_level = function(p) sprintf("p = %.2g", p)
  )

Pie Chart

data <- data.frame(
  group=LETTERS[1:5],
  value=c(13,7,9,21,2)
)

head(data)
##   group value
## 1     A    13
## 2     B     7
## 3     C     9
## 4     D    21
## 5     E     2
# Compute the position of labels
data <- data %>% 
  arrange(desc(group)) %>%
  mutate(prop = value / sum(data$value) *100) %>%
  mutate(ypos = cumsum(prop)- 0.5*prop )

# Basic piechart
ggplot(data, aes(x="", y=prop, fill=group)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", width=1, color="white") +
  coord_polar("y", start=0) +
  theme_void() + 
  theme(legend.position="none") +
  
  geom_text(aes(y = ypos, label = group), color = "white", size=4) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette="Set1")

Flow

Sankey Plot

# Basic

library(networkD3)
library(tidyverse)
library(viridis)
library(patchwork)
library(hrbrthemes)
library(circlize)


# A connection data frame is a list of flows with intensity for each flow
links <- data.frame(
  source=c("group_A","group_A", "group_B", "group_C", "group_C", "group_E"), 
  target=c("group_C","group_D", "group_E", "group_F", "group_G", "group_H"), 
  value=c(2,3, 2, 3, 1, 3)
  )

head(links)
##    source  target value
## 1 group_A group_C     2
## 2 group_A group_D     3
## 3 group_B group_E     2
## 4 group_C group_F     3
## 5 group_C group_G     1
## 6 group_E group_H     3
# From these flows we need to create a node data frame: it lists every entities involved in the flow
nodes <- data.frame(
  name=c(as.character(links$source), 
  as.character(links$target)) %>% unique()
)

head(nodes)
##      name
## 1 group_A
## 2 group_B
## 3 group_C
## 4 group_E
## 5 group_D
## 6 group_F
# With networkD3, connection must be provided using id, not using real name like in the links dataframe.. So we need to reformat it.
links$IDsource <- match(links$source, nodes$name)-1 
links$IDtarget <- match(links$target, nodes$name)-1
 
# Make the Network
sankeyNetwork(Links = links, Nodes = nodes,
              Source = "IDsource", Target = "IDtarget",
              Value = "value", NodeID = "name", 
              sinksRight=FALSE)

# I need a long format
data_long <- data %>%
  rownames_to_column %>%
  gather(key = 'key', value = 'value', -rowname) %>%
  filter(value > 0)
colnames(data_long) <- c("source", "target", "value")
data_long$target <- paste(data_long$target, " ", sep="")

head(data_long)
##            source     target    value
## 1          Africa    Africa  3.142471
## 2       East Asia East.Asia  1.630997
## 3      South Asia East.Asia  0.525881
## 4 South East Asia East.Asia  0.145264
## 5          Africa    Europe  2.107883
## 6       East Asia    Europe  0.601265
# From these flows we need to create a node data frame: it lists every entities involved in the flow
nodes <- data.frame(name=c(as.character(data_long$source), as.character(data_long$target)) %>% unique())

head(nodes)
##              name
## 1          Africa
## 2       East Asia
## 3      South Asia
## 4 South East Asia
## 5          Europe
## 6   Latin America
# With networkD3, connection must be provided using id, not using real name like in the links dataframe.. So we need to reformat it.
data_long$IDsource=match(data_long$source, nodes$name)-1 
data_long$IDtarget=match(data_long$target, nodes$name)-1

# prepare colour scale
ColourScal ='d3.scaleOrdinal() .range(["#FDE725FF","#B4DE2CFF","#6DCD59FF","#35B779FF","#1F9E89FF","#26828EFF","#31688EFF","#3E4A89FF","#482878FF","#440154FF"])'

# Make the Network
sankeyNetwork(Links = data_long, Nodes = nodes,
                     Source = "IDsource", Target = "IDtarget",
                     Value = "value", NodeID = "name", 
                     sinksRight=FALSE, colourScale=ColourScal, nodeWidth=40, fontSize=13, nodePadding=20)
